OL,4,Cprison for harassing four victims
OL,6,FThe second offence, against the same
OL,7,Fvictim, relates solely to social media
OL,8,Fposts.
OL,10,FThe indictment for the fifth offence
OL,11,Fstates that Sutcliffe sent numerous
OL,12,Funwanted messages as well as uploading
OL,13,Fsocial media posts about the victim,
OL,14,Fcausing her to feel harassed, alarmed
OL,15,Fand distressed.
OL,17,FDistrict Judge Hollins told him on
OL,18,FWednesday that the case would be
OL,19,Fadjourned to allow her to familiarise
OL,20,Fherself with the background.
